    "body": "This PR implements `cudax::composite_mapping` that allows to combine multiple mappings into one. This can allow the user to skip creating intermediate groups and allows much more flexibility. Users are not expected to create the `composite_mapping` instance directly, but rather by using the pipe operator `|`. For example:\r\n```cpp\r\ncudax::group g{cuda::gpu_thread, cuda::this_warp{config}, cudax::group_by<4>{} | cudax::group_as<1, 3>{}, cudax::lane_synchronizer{});\r\n```\r\nSplits warp into `16` groups of counts `1` or `3`.\r\n\r\nDepends on #8755",
    "created_at": "2026-04-30T16:57:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-05T04:44:36Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-05T04:44:36Z",
